The paper deals with the problem of distributed decision-making in networks, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The focus on local decision-making algorithms also suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC). The analysis of different variations of the model, including the role of identifiers, involves information theory (cs.IT).
